author: Slidebean
description:
How online power became one of the world’s most dangerous forces.

Wired’s 2025 list highlights a fundamental shift in digital risk:
the most dangerous actors online are no longer individual cybercriminals, but political figures, institutions, and nation states.

As digital influence increasingly drives real world outcomes from elections to public safety, the challenge is no longer just cybersecurity, but accountability at scale.

title: The internet’s most dangerous people aren’t hackers anymore
